{"id":"math230-dot_prod230-003","cid":"MATH 230","topic":"Vectors in 3D","subtopic":"Dot product","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Compute the dot product: ({a1}, {a2}, {a3}) · ({b1}, {b2}, {b3}). Are these vectors orthogonal?","params":{"a1":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3},"a2":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3},"a3":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3},"b1":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3},"b2":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3},"b3":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"dot_prod230","steps":["Dot product = ({a1})({b1}) + ({a2})({b2}) + ({a3})({b3}) = {answer_dot_prod230}.","If dot product = 0 the vectors are orthogonal; otherwise they are not."],"tags":["calculus-3","vectors","dot-product","orthogonal"]}
